Explanation of Architecture
🔹 1. Base EC2 Instance
Initial server where:
Apache (httpd) is installed
Web application is configured
Acts as the master template
🔹 2. Golden AMI (Amazon Machine Image)
Image created from configured EC2 instance
Contains:
OS
Installed software
Application files

👉 This ensures same configuration everywhere

🔹 3. Multiple EC2 Instances
Created using the Golden AMI
Example:
Webserver 1
Webserver 2

👉 All instances are identical

🔹 4. Web Servers (Apache)
Each EC2 instance runs Apache
Hosts the same application
🔹 5. Application Access
Each instance has a public IP
Users can access the application via browser
🔹 6. Private S3 Bucket (Optional)
Used for:
Backup
Storing files
Not directly part of deployment flow
🔥 Key Features of This Architecture

✅ Consistent server configuration
✅ Faster deployment of instances
✅ Reusability using AMI
✅ Scalable infrastructure
✅ Reduced manual setup
